{"article_id":"V9HFZNsk59zH2x7T","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"DES MOINES , Iowa -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Bernie Sanders ,","depth":11},{"id":2,"text":"riding an updraft of insurgent passion in Iowa ,","depth":11},{"id":3,"text":"has closed to within 7 points of Hillary Clinton in the Democratic presidential race .","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"She ' s the first choice of 37 % of likely Democratic caucusgoers ;","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"he ' s the pick for 30 % ,","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"according to a new Des Moines Register/Bloomberg Politics Iowa Poll .","depth":12},{"id":7,"text":"But Clinton has lost a third of her supporters since May , a trajectory","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":9,"text":"if sustained","depth":13},{"id":10,"text":"puts her at risk","depth":13},{"id":11,"text":"of losing again in Iowa , the initial crucible in the presidential nominating contest .","depth":13},{"id":12,"text":"This is the first time","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Clinton , the former secretary of state and longtime presumptive front-runner , has dropped below the 50 % mark in four polls","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"conducted by the Register and Bloomberg Politics this year .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"Poll results include Vice President Joe Biden as a choice ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"although he has not yet decided whether to join the race .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Biden captures 14 % , five months from the first-in-the-nation vote Feb. 1 .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Even without Biden in the mix ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"Clinton falls below a majority , at 43 % .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"\" This feels like 2008 all over again , \"","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"said J. Ann Selzer , pollster for the Iowa Poll .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"In that race , Clinton led John Edwards by 6 percentage points and Barack Obama by 7 points in an early October Iowa Poll .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"But Obama ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"buoyed by younger voters and first-time caucusgoers ,","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"surged ahead by late November .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"In this cycle , Sanders is attracting more first-time caucusgoers than Clinton .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"He claims 43 % of their vote","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"compared with 31 % for Clinton .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"He also leads by 23 percentage points with the under-45 crowd and by 21 points among independent voters .","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"Sanders , a Vermont U.S. senator , has become a liberal Pied Piper in Iowa not as a vote against Clinton ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"but because caucusgoers genuinely like him ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"the poll shows .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"An overwhelming 96 % of his backers say","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"they support him and his ideas .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Just 2 % say","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"they ' re motivated by opposition to Clinton .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Back in January , half of likely Democratic caucusgoers were unfamiliar with Sanders ,","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"who has been elected to Congress for 25 years as an independent .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"He has jumped from 5 % support in January to 30 % .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"Clinton , a famous public figure for decades , has dropped in that period from 56 % to 37 % .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"\" These numbers would suggest","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"that she can be beaten , \"","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"said Steve McMahon , a Virginia-based Democratic strategist","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"who has worked on presidential campaigns","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"dating to 1980 .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"\" But , \"","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"he added ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"\" it ' s still early ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"and Hillary Clinton ' s done this before .","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"She knows","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"what it takes","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"to win . \"","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"If Clinton survives the caucus and primary gauntlet","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"to become the nominee ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"nearly two-thirds of likely Democratic caucusgoers say","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"they ' re \" mostly confident \"","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"she can win the general election .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"About 24 % are mostly nervous ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"and 9 % aren ' t sure .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"The open question is what Biden will see in these results .","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Will he see a teetering front-runner in distress ?","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Or that Sanders has already consolidated a big share of the support","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"available to a Clinton alternative ?","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"In a May Iowa Poll ,","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"just before his eldest son , Beau , died of brain cancer at age 46 ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"8 % of likely caucusgoers listed Biden as their first choice for president .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"A Biden bid also would open a two-front war for Clinton .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"If he were to declare a candidacy ,","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"he ' d almost certainly get a bump in his numbers .","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"The vice president saps support from both Clinton and Sanders ,","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"the poll shows .","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"Without Biden in the mix ,","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"Clinton is at 43 %","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"and Sanders is at 35 % .","depth":14},{"id":75,"text":"\" So , Biden takes 6 points from Clinton and 5 points from Sanders , \"","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Selzer said .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"The Iowa Poll of 404 likely Democratic caucusgoers was conducted Aug. 23-26 by Selzer & Co. of Des Moines .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"The margin of error is plus or minus 4.9 percentage points .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"\" Voters right now are flocking to the angry , authentic outsiders","depth":6},{"id":80,"text":"and moving away from the cautious or calculating establishment insiders , \"","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"McMahon said .","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"Clinton has been dogged by media questions and an FBI investigation","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"about whether her use of a private , home-based email server while secretary of state undermined U.S. security .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"In Iowa on Wednesday , she said","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"use of personal email \" clearly wasn ' t the best choice. \"","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"But Clinton ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"who says","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"voters don ' t bring up the issue ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"downplays the investigation as \" about politics . \"","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Selzer said","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"Clinton is right about the unimportance of the email controversy at this point in the caucus race","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"- 76 % of her supporters and 61 % of all likely Democratic caucusgoers say","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"it ' s not important to them .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"The emails are at least somewhat important to 28 % of all likely caucusgoers ,","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"with an additional 10 % saying","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"the issue is very important .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"\" The stuff with the emails - that doesn ' t bother me , \"","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"said poll respondent Craig Glassmeyer , 50 , a screen printer from Cedar Rapids .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"\" It ' s just being politicized , as well as Benghazi .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"How could it have been her fault ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"you know ?","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"They really don ' t want Hillary in there ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"and so they ' re fighting","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"as hard","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"as they can","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"to block her nomination . \"","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Still , Glassmeyer is one of the 14 %","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"who say","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"they ' re not sure who their choice is yet","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"or are uncommitted .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"He ' s trying to decide between Clinton and Sanders ,","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"\" who may be too liberal for me , \"","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"Meanwhile , three candidates are in danger","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"of not meeting viability thresholds in the Democratic caucuses .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"Martin O ' Malley ,","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"who campaigns on the progressive results","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"he achieved as Baltimore ' s mayor and Maryland ' s governor ,","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"has 3 % support .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"Jim Webb , a former U.S. senator from Virginia","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"who stresses his military experience as a Marine and later a Pentagon official under President Ronald Reagan ,","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"is at 2 % .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"And Lincoln Chafee , an ex-Republican and former Rhode Island governor with an anti-war message , gets 1 % .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"Selzer noted","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"that 39 % of likely caucusgoers say","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"their feelings about Sanders are very favorable ,","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"with another 34 % saying","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"mostly favorable .","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"Only 8 % have a negative view of Sanders .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"Contrast that with Clinton :","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Fewer feel very favorable about her","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"( 27 % ) ,","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"and twice as many view her negatively","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"( 19 % ) .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Still , she ' s doing better than in fall 2007 ,","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"when she was viewed negatively by 30 % of likely Democratic caucusgoers .","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Poll respondents say","depth":4},{"id":138,"text":"they ' re wild about Sanders","depth":5},{"id":139,"text":"because of his authenticity , refusal","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"to run a negative campaign","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"and his big ideas ,","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"which include government-paid college tuition and health care for all .","depth":7},{"id":143,"text":"\" He doesn ' t sugarcoat anything ,","depth":5},{"id":144,"text":"and he has answers to actual questions .","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"He doesn ' t just use talking points , \"","depth":6},{"id":146,"text":"said Deb Bolfik , a 41-year-old grocery store worker from Des Moines","depth":5},{"id":147,"text":"who intends to support Sanders in the caucuses .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":295,"left":0,"right":294,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":294,"left":283,"right":293,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":228,"right":282,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":225,"right":227,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":176,"right":224,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":166,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":161,"right":165,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":158,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":150,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":152,"right":156,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity"